ReviewContent: The Mojo Lounge was a really good time. We went with some friends and it was incredible. It was a Sunday night, acoustic open mic night. The place was full of musicians and music lovers. As a musician myself, not of any great talent, but nonetheless able to put together a guitar strum and sing a little song, I was interested in trying the place out. What I discovered there was a Mecca of amateur guitar songwriting talent. I was warmly welcomed and encouraged to try my hand there. There were even guitars available for me to use. In the end, I declined because I didnt really have anything ready. Now I regret that decision. Nonetheless, the beer was great, the people were lovely, and the experience was overwhelmingly enjoyable. Next time I go there, on a Sunday night, rest assured Ill be playing! If you choose to go to the Mojo Lounge, choose to do so on a Sunday night. Parking: Some of the back spots are tight to maneuver.
